oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Elise Croft and friend
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Elise Croft and a friend sit in the yard of the Croft house in Havana with their backs to the camera. The girls are leaning towards each other as if one is telling a secret to the other. A fence and gate can be seen in the background. Written on this page is "26 F St. Vedado- Thursday, June 6, 1907-."
This is the first of two houses the Crofts owned in Havana, located at 26 F Street in Vedado. The second house was located at the corner of 19 and F Streets, Vedado.
